00029 struct b2056_inittab_entry {
00030         /* Value to write if we use the 5GHz band. */
00031         u16 ghz5;
00032         /* Value to write if we use the 2.4GHz band. */
00033         u16 ghz2;
00034         /* Flags */
00035         u8 flags;
00036 };
00037 #define B2056_INITTAB_ENTRY_OK  0x01
00038 #define B2056_INITTAB_UPLOAD    0x02
00039 #define UPLOAD          .flags = B2056_INITTAB_ENTRY_OK | B2056_INITTAB_UPLOAD
00040 #define NOUPLOAD        .flags = B2056_INITTAB_ENTRY_OK
00041 
00042 struct b2056_inittabs_pts {
00043         const struct b2056_inittab_entry *syn;
00044         unsigned int syn_length;
00045         const struct b2056_inittab_entry *tx;
00046         unsigned int tx_length;
00047         const struct b2056_inittab_entry *rx;
00048         unsigned int rx_length;
00049 };

09013 
09014 static void b2056_upload_inittab(struct b43_wldev *dev, bool ghz5,
09015                                  bool ignore_uploadflag, u16 routing,
09016                                  const struct b2056_inittab_entry *e,
09017                                  unsigned int length)
09018 {
09019         unsigned int i;
09020         u16 value;
09021 
09022         for (i = 0; i < length; i++, e++) {
09023                 if (!(e->flags & B2056_INITTAB_ENTRY_OK))
09024                         continue;
09025                 if ((e->flags & B2056_INITTAB_UPLOAD) || ignore_uploadflag) {
09026                         if (ghz5)
09027                                 value = e->ghz5;
09028                         else
09029                                 value = e->ghz2;
09030                         b43_radio_write(dev, routing | i, value);
09031                 }
09032         }
09033 }

09035 void b2056_upload_inittabs(struct b43_wldev *dev,
09036                            bool ghz5, bool ignore_uploadflag)
09037 {
09038         struct b2056_inittabs_pts *pts;
09039 
09040         if (dev->phy.rev >= ARRAY_SIZE(b2056_inittabs)) {
09041                 B43_WARN_ON(1);
09042                 return;
09043         }
09044         pts = &b2056_inittabs[dev->phy.rev];
09045 
09046         b2056_upload_inittab(dev, ghz5, ignore_uploadflag,
09047                                 B2056_SYN, pts->syn, pts->syn_length);
09048         b2056_upload_inittab(dev, ghz5, ignore_uploadflag,
09049                                 B2056_TX0, pts->tx, pts->tx_length);
09050         b2056_upload_inittab(dev, ghz5, ignore_uploadflag,
09051                                 B2056_TX1, pts->tx, pts->tx_length);
09052         b2056_upload_inittab(dev, ghz5, ignore_uploadflag,
09053                                 B2056_RX0, pts->rx, pts->rx_length);
09054         b2056_upload_inittab(dev, ghz5, ignore_uploadflag,
09055                                 B2056_RX1, pts->rx, pts->rx_length);
09056 }

09058 const struct b43_nphy_channeltab_entry_rev3 *
09059 b43_nphy_get_chantabent_rev3(struct b43_wldev *dev, u16 freq)
09060 {
09061         const struct b43_nphy_channeltab_entry_rev3 *e;
09062         unsigned int length, i;
09063 
09064         switch (dev->phy.rev) {
09065         case 3:
09066                 e = b43_nphy_channeltab_rev3;
09067                 length = ARRAY_SIZE(b43_nphy_channeltab_rev3);
09068                 break;
09069         case 4:
09070                 e = b43_nphy_channeltab_rev4;
09071                 length = ARRAY_SIZE(b43_nphy_channeltab_rev4);
09072                 break;
09073         case 5:
09074                 e = b43_nphy_channeltab_rev5;
09075                 length = ARRAY_SIZE(b43_nphy_channeltab_rev5);
09076                 break;
09077         case 6:
09078                 e = b43_nphy_channeltab_rev6;
09079                 length = ARRAY_SIZE(b43_nphy_channeltab_rev6);
09080                 break;
09081         case 7:
09082         case 9:
09083                 e = b43_nphy_channeltab_rev7_9;
09084                 length = ARRAY_SIZE(b43_nphy_channeltab_rev7_9);
09085                 break;
09086         case 8:
09087                 e = b43_nphy_channeltab_rev8;
09088                 length = ARRAY_SIZE(b43_nphy_channeltab_rev8);
09089                 break;
09090         default:
09091                 B43_WARN_ON(1);
09092                 return NULL;
09093         }
09094 
09095         for (i = 0; i < length; i++, e++) {
09096                 if (e->freq == freq)
09097                         return e;
09098         }
09099 
09100         return NULL;
09101 }
